    "department": "Deliveroo Cost Center Hierarchy",
    "description": "About the team and the Role\n\nThe New Verticals Associate is a crucial role within the Deliveroo Skills Centre, focusing on mission-critical operational tasks. This position contributes significantly to maintaining the quality and integrity of our platform by executing a diverse range of responsibilities and supporting Deliveroo's ambitious expansion into new on-demand grocery and retail services. The Associate reports directly to the Skills Centre - Squad Lead.\n\nWhat you'll be doing\n\n - Content Moderation: Identify and remove prohibited items from the platform, ensuring strict compliance with Deliveroo's policies and standards.\n\n - Marketing Campaign Execution: Assist in the implementation of marketing campaigns across various platforms, ensuring accuracy and consistency.\n\n - Menu Management: Upload and manage menu items, ensuring data accuracy and consistency across the platform.\n\n - Competitor Analysis: Conduct thorough competitor analysis to support strategic decision-making and maintain Deliveroo's competitive edge.\n\n - Partner Onboarding \u0026 Profile Management: Efficiently manage high-volume partner profile setups, ensuring accuracy and swift integration under strict time constraints.\n\n - Autonomous Category Management: Strategically manage product categories by analyzing data, leveraging self-derived insights, and adhering to SOP guidelines to optimize structure and performance.\n\n - Versatile Task Execution: Adaptably manage diverse operational tasks concurrently in a dynamic live environment, demonstrating a readiness to independently acquire new proficiencies.\n\n*The responsibilities listed are not exhaustive and subject to change as priorities within the business change.\n\nRequirements\n\n - Detail-Oriented \u0026 Compliant: Possesses a meticulous approach ensuring accuracy and adherence to Standard Operating Procedures (SOPs).\n\n - Organized \u0026 Efficient: Proven ability to multitask, prioritize tasks effectively, and meet deadlines consistently.\n\n - Spreadsheet Proficiency: Strong skills in Google Sheets (or MS Excel) for data analysis and manipulation.\n\n - Task Management Software Experience: Familiarity with workflow and tracking tools, specifically monday.com http://monday.com.\n\n - Strong Communication: Demonstrates clear and effective English communication, both written and verbal, for collaborative environments.\n\n - Proactive Discrepancy Reporting: Ability to identify and report discrepancies in real-time to relevant stakeholders or reporting channels for immediate time optimization.\n\n - Problem-Solving \u0026 Optimization: An agile self-starter, capable of quickly grasping new tasks, identifying effective workarounds, and implementing time optimization techniques to minimize task timelines.\n\nWhy Deliveroo\n\nOur mission is to transform the way you shop and eat, bringing the neighbourhood to your door by connecting consumers, restaurants, shops and riders. We are transforming the way the world eats and shops by making access to food and products more convenient and enjoyable. We give people the opportunity to buy what they want, as they want it, when and where they want it.\n\nWe are a technology-driven company at the forefront of the most rapidly expanding industry in the world. We are still a small team, making a very large impact, looking to answer some of the most interesting questions out there. We move fast, value autonomy and ownership, and we are always looking for new ideas.\n\n\nCAREER PROGRESSION \u0026 BENEFITS\n\nAt Deliveroo, we are committed to the growth and development of our employees. This role offers unique opportunities including:\n\n - Continuous Skill Enhancement: Access to training programs to enhance skills and knowledge in operational tasks and tools.\n\n - Mentorship Opportunities: Guidance and support from experienced professionals across the organization.\n\n - Clear Advancement Pathways: Defined opportunities for career advancement within the Skills Centre and other departments, based on performance and interest.\n\n - Development Resources: Access to workshops and resources to develop new skills relevant to the role and future career aspirations.\n\nWorkplace \u0026 Diversity\n\nDeliveroo prioritizes the welfare of its employees and offers a competitive range of benefits. We champion a diverse and inclusive workplace, welcoming individuals of all backgrounds. A passion for food and a desire to contribute to a fast-growing, exciting industry are key.",
    "employment_type": "FullTime",
